<!--
  E-MU Z-Plane Filter Types — Machine-Readable Reference
  Source: Emulator X3 Reference Manual, Chapter 6 (Voice Processing), pp. 145–153
  Extracted: 2026-04-16

  This file documents all 55 factory filter types available in the E-MU
  Emulator X / Proteus 2000 / Audity 2000 Z-plane filter engine.

  The Z-plane filter has the unique ability to change its function over time.
  Filters A and B represent two different complex filters or "frames."
  Most filters have two parameters: Frequency (or Morph) and Resonance (Q, Gain, Body Size).
  These two parameters can be continuously varied during the note.

  Categories:
    BPF  — Band-pass filter
    DST  — Distortion
    EQ+  — EQ boost filter
    EQ-  — EQ cut filter
    FLG  — Flanger filter
    HPF  — High-pass filter
    LPF  — Low-pass filter
    PHA  — Phaser filter
    PROG — Programmable (user-defined morph)
    REZ  — Highly resonant
    SFX  — Special effect
    VOW  — Vowel / formant
    WAH  — Wah-Wah pedal
-->
<emu-zplane-filters
  source="Emulator X3 Reference Manual"
  chapter="6 — Voice Processing"
  total-types="55"
  includes-no-filter="true">

